    "updated_at": "2016-06-07T08:32:40Z",
    "body": "Is not an ideal solution, but until this issue gets fixed at Chrome, you can try the following workaround: \n\nAfter changing the provider, use Javascript to change the caret position, making it go over every word.\n\nThis works since moving the caret forces the spellchecker to re-evaluate every word _touched_ by the caret.\n"
